obj_root_law_sections_4:
  sectionId (35551)
  sectionNo (4)
  orderNo 4
  title `Payment to be charged on the Consolidated Fund of India.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00041_197924_1528449325673&sectionId=35551&sectionno=4&orderno=4&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00041_197924_1528449325673
obj_root_law_sections_4_content:
  string
  line `The expenditure on the payments`
  line `in pursuance of section 3 shall be charged on the Consolidated Fund of India.`
obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_5:
  sectionId (35552)
  sectionNo (5)
  orderNo 5
  title `Power to make rules.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00041_197924_1528449325673&sectionId=35552&sectionno=5&orderno=5&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00041_197924_1528449325673
obj_root_law_sections_5_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette,`
  line `make rules providing for the time at which and the manner in which, any payments under this Act are to`
  line `be made, for the making of adjustments between one financial year andanother and for`
  line `any other incidental or ancillary matters.`
  line
  line `(2) Every rule made under this section shall be laid, as soon as may be after it is made, before each`
  line `House of Parliament, while it is in session, for a total period of thirty days which may be comprised in`
  line `one session or in two or more successive sessions, and if, before the expiry of the session immediately`
  line `following the session or the successive sessions aforesaid, both Houses agree in making any modification`
  line `in the rule or both Houses agree that the rule should not be made, the rule shall thereafter have effect only`
  line `in such modified form or be of no effect, as the case may be; so, however, that any such modification of`
  line `annulment shall be without prejudice to the validity of anything previously done under that rule.`
obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_6:
  sectionId (35553)
  sectionNo (6)
  orderNo 6
  title Repeal.
  content obj_root_law_sections_6_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00041_197924_1528449325673&sectionId=35553&sectionno=6&orderno=6&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00041_197924_1528449325673
obj_root_law_sections_6_content:
  string
  line `The Union Duties of Excise (Distribution) Act, 1962 (3 of 1962), shall, as from the`
  line `1st day of April, 1979 stand repealed.`
obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes:
  string
  line
